#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
SGA2025-build-catalog: merge the SGA beta catalog, NED cross-match results,
DESI DR1 redshifts, and LVD distances/velocities into a unified per-region
FITS catalog.

Redshift resolution
-------------------
For each galaxy a single "best" DESI spectrum is selected:

  0. Proximity filter: only spectra within --desi-max-sep arcsec of the SGA
     center (TARGET_RA/DEC) are considered, excluding background/foreground
     objects whose fiber happens to fall inside the SGA ellipse.
  1. Deduplicate with ZCAT_PRIMARY=True (DESI's highest-S/N coadd per TARGETID).
  2. Prefer SPECTYPE='GALAXY' AND ZWARN=0.
  3. Fall back to ZWARN=0 with any SPECTYPE.
  4. Among survivors, pick the highest DELTACHI2.

     Note: target-bit logic (e.g. BGS_TARGET != 0) could be used to break
     ties before DELTACHI2, but is omitted because secondary-program
     observations are equally valid redshift sources.

  If no ZWARN=0 spectrum survives, Z_IVAR_DESI=0 (no adopted DESI redshift).

The adopted redshift (Z) priority is LVD > DESI > NED:
  - LVD  when Z_LVD  != 0.  (vlos_systemic / C_LIGHT; Z_IVAR_LVD may be 0.)
  - DESI when Z_IVAR_DESI > 0
  - NED  when Z_IVAR_NED  > 0
A Z_FLAG bit is set when any two measured redshifts differ by more than
--vdiff-threshold km/s.

Sentinels
---------
  Redshifts / IVARs : 0.   (Z_IVAR=0 => no measurement; Z=0 means either no
                             measurement or a genuine z≈0 for very nearby galaxies
                             — always use Z_IVAR>0 to test for a valid redshift)
  Other floats      : -1.  (strictly negative, unphysical for dist/separation)
  Integer IDs       : -1
  Strings           : ''   (blank)

  NED_Z_UNC=0 in NED means "error not reported" (common in older catalogs).
  These entries are assigned a nominal Z_IVAR_NED = (1 / NED_Z_NOMINAL_ERR)^2
  rather than being treated as missing.

  DIST_NED_IVAR=0 means either no NED distance or no formal distance
  uncertainty was reported (unlike redshifts, no nominal default is assumed).

Dtype validation
----------------
Every column in the beta catalog is checked against SGA_datamodel; any dtype
mismatch is corrected before writing (known case: REGION int64 -> int16).

Output
------
  {outdir}/SGA2025-{region}.fits   (EXTNAME='SGA2025')

Examples
--------
  SGA2025-build-catalog --neddir /path/nedquery \\
                         --redshiftdir /path/redshifts \\
                         --outdir /path/output

  SGA2025-build-catalog --region dr11-south --vdiff-threshold 500 \\
                         --desi-max-sep 5 \\
                         --neddir /path/nedquery \\
                         --redshiftdir /path/redshifts \\
                         --outdir /path/output \\
                         --lvd-catalog /path/lvd_comb_all_v1.1.0.ecsv


SGA2025-build-catalog --neddir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/nedquery \
  --redshiftdir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/redshifts \
  --outdir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample \
  --lvd-catalog=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/nedquery/lvd_comb_all_v1.1.0.ecsv

